Sure! Here's a simple test code for the ESP32 that blinks an LED connected to pin 2:


```cpp
void setup() {
  pinMode(2, OUTPUT); // Set pin 2 as an output
}

void loop() {
  digitalWrite(2, HIGH); // Turn the LED on
  delay(1000);           // Wait for a second
  digitalWrite(2, LOW);  // Turn the LED off
  delay(1000);           // Wait for a second
}
```

You can upload this code using the Arduino IDE. Just make sure you have the correct board selected in the tools menu. Would you like more details on how to set it up?
